</P>
<P>
   About two weeks before the event, give yourself a haircut
following these rules:
</P>
<P>
   a) You cannot look in the mirror while you cut your hair.
</P>
<P>
   b) Your hair must be dry when you cut it (for more dead ends).
</P>
<P>
   c) Try to use the dullest scissors you can find. A pocket knife
is even better.
</P>
<P>
   (Begin italics)Once at the event:(End italics)
</P>
<P>
   Go to the nearest water source. A horse trough is great, but
your canteen will be adequate. Soak your head. Then, pull your hat
down real tight and let dry.
</P>
<P>
   (Begin italics)Now for the beard:(End italics)
</P>
<P>
   Chew tobacco. Don't spit; drool instead.
</P>
<P>
   Eat a lot of cornbread, allowing the crumbs to collect in the
tobacco juice. This provides a nice textured look, plus it makes a
