Kippur war _ particularly the contest of 1996, when Netanyahu was
elected.
</P>
<P>
   That campaign was viewed as a political watershed for a nation
whose very existence seemed once again in peril. It was fought in
the aftermath of the assassination of Yitzhak Rabin, the prime
minister who made peace with Yasser Arafat, and was shadowed by
random Arab terrorist bombings that Netanyahu incorporated into his
