   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Sunday, May 16. If you
haveany questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) _ When the time comes for her trial, the
accused murderer Kelly Blake won't be hauled into court in
shackles. Authorities have overwhelming evidence that Blake cruelly
slaughtered two of her own children and tried to kill a third, and
for that, prosecutors would love to lead her around in irons. But,
they can't. The manacles would slip off the stumps. By E.J.
MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
