<P>
   FISHER-FESTIVAL (Frontenac, Kan. _) On April 10 residents of
Frontenac, a southeast Kansas town, turned out in droves for what's
called Festa Italiana. They brought home-cooked dishes and raised
$35,500. That money _ and money realized from future festivals _
will guarantee scholarships to graduates of Frontenac High.
</P>
<P>
   BOAT-SAFETY (Lake Ozark, Mo. _) On Memorial Day the Lake of the
Ozarks will be overrun by boaters _ as many as 40,000. The summer
boating season will bring the threat of more serious injuries and
even deaths.
</P>
<P>
   Missouri is one of the most dangerous states for boaters,
according to an analysis of U.S. Coast Guard data. The agency
tracks serious accidents, those involving injury or death, or
damage exceeding $500.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-SPEED (Kansas City, Mo. _) Two weeks ago Shane Seley
took a blind leap into the uncharted future of cyberspace, a step
that thousands of Kansas Citians are eager to take.
</P>
<P>
   He bought a cable modem.
</P>
<P>
   Seley is one of 400 early-bird testers of Time Warner's Road
Runner, one of two services that will begin delivering high-speed
Internet access to Kansas City homes in the next two months.
</P>
