<HEADER>
A8916 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-RAC-PREAKNESS-TEX     05-15 0740
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAC-PREAKNESS-TEX </SLUG>
 
Charismatic quiets Derby critics 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY MOSS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
BALTIMORE _ This time, Charismatic left no doubt.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Considered by most a lucky winner of the Kentucky Derby two
weeks ago, the underrated colt blew away his opposition in
yesterday's Preakness Stakes to set the stage for another Triple
Crown chase.
</P>
<P>
   Four other horses had more money wagered on them than 8-to-1
Charismatic, but the former claiming horse carried jockey Chris
Antley to a 11/2-length victory over favored Menifee, whom he had
beaten by only a neck at the Derby. Badge ran third at 58-to-1
odds.
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic now heads to the mile-and-a-half Belmont Stakes on
June 5 as the third consecutive Preakness winner to have a chance
at sweeping the Triple Crown. Silver Charm won the first two legs
in 1997, then lost the Belmont to Touch Gold. Real Quiet was upset
in last year's Belmont by Victory Gallop.
</P>
<P>
   And for the second time in three years, beer distributor Bob
Lewis of Newport Beach, Calif., and his wife, Beverly, have a
chance at the Triple Crown, which has been accomplished only 11
times and not since 1978's Affirmed. The Lewises own Charismatic
and raced Silver Charm.
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic could very well add his name to that list by winning
the Belmont, said trainer D. Wayne Lukas, who won the Preakness for
the fifth time and continued his decade-long dominance of
3-year-old classic races.
</P>
<P>
   ``Before the Derby,'' recalled Lukas, ``I told Bob and Beverly,
`I don't know about the first two, but I sure like him in the
Belmont.' ''
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic will earn his owners a $5 million bonus if he wins
the Triple Crown.
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic's Kentucky Derby victory was diminished by troubles
that befell numerous other runners in the crowded 19-horse field.
But yesterday, before a crowd of 100,311, he had more adversity
than anyone and overcame it with a brilliant performance.
</P>
<P>
   Antley took him five-wide around the second turn of Pimlico Race
Course, even though the inside path next to the rail was much
faster than the rest of the track. No horse in two days had won at
Pimlico with a move that wide, but Charismatic swept past his
rivals with a bold rush.
</P>
<P>
   Although the outcome was similar, Pimlico's fast rail created a
vastly different pace scenario than the slow-paced Derby. In an
attempt to capitalize on the fast rail, Kimberlite Pipe, Cat Thief
and Vicar were all sent for the lead and dueled through fast
fractions of 45.27 seconds for a half-mile and 1:10.31 for six
furlongs.
</P>
<P>
   That set the stage for closers to prevail. Badge was far back in
the early running, too, as was fourth-place Stephen Got Even.
</P>
<P>
   But in the end, it again came down to Charismatic and Menifee.
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic actually caught and passed Menifee, who was gaining
on him at the end of the Kentucky Derby. Menifee raced in eighth
place in the 13-horse field for the first half-mile, while
Charismatic was behind and outside him in 10th.
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic's big move past Menifee propelled him to a
three-length advantage in midstretch.
</P>
<P>
   But unlike the Derby, said Pat Day, who rode Menifee, ``We
didn't close up any ground on the winner in the last sixteenth of a
mile.''
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic, timed in 1:55 2-5 for the 13/16 miles, paid $18.60
to win. His 8-to-1 Preakness odds were the second highest for a
Derby winner, behind only Dark Star, who was 11-to-1 in the 1953
Preakness and ran sixth.
</P>
<P>
   In the Kentucky Derby, Charismatic paid $64.60.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is damn near better than the beer business,'' said Bob
Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   ``Some loyal followers are getting their car payments done and
putting their kids through college if they stuck with this one,''
Lukas said.
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic is the 28th horse to win the first two legs of the
Triple Crown. Eleven had gone on to win the Belmont.
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic gave Lukas a record 12th victory in a Triple Crown
race, and his ninth in the 1990s. In one span during 1994-1996, he
won six consecutive. Although Lukas has never trained a horse that
swept the Triple Crown, he won all three races in 1995 with two
different horses, Thunder Gulch and Timber Country.
</P>
<P>
   ``Now maybe my turn has come up that we can do it with one
horse,'' Lukas said.
</P>
<P>
   After yesterday's clear-cut result, Charismatic will have far
fewer doubters.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to go home and read that the best horse won,'' Lukas
said.
</P>
<P>
   The best horse won.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
