<HEADER>
A8958 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN     05-16 0764
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NO RICE, NO PROBLEM FOR LAKERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ Some symbolic gestures need no translation: Kobe
Bryant's dead-cold stare amid a deadly hot shooting streak. J.R.
Reid's crunching clothesline foul of an airborne Scottie Pippen.
The chest-to-ribs bump between Derek Harper and Shaquille O'Neal.
</P>
<P>
   These were the images of a team that let an opportunity slip
away _ that wouldn't let the same opportunity slide by twice.
Images of a team so steeped in confidence, even the loss of their
best shooter would not deter them.
</P>
<P>
   You could have watched the Lakers with the volume off Saturday
and known from the opening tipoff that they were set to eject the
Houston Rockets out of the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   The job they failed to finish two days earlier was completed
without hesitation and no room for doubt, as the Lakers finished
off the Rockets with a 98-88 victory at Compaq Center, earning a
pass to San Antonio for the Western Conference semifinals.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers finished off the Rockets in Game 4, a bit later than
they had hoped, but no less satisfying at the conclusion.
</P>
<P>
   ``We wanted to finish it off in Game 3 _ that would have shown a
lot more,'' said Bryant. ``But we did do a good job of coming in
here and putting them away.''
</P>
<P>
   They did it with everything they had and without one thing they
had relied on. Glen Rice was out with a sore right elbow, replaced
at the last minute by Rick Fox in the starting lineup.
</P>
<P>
   But the Rockets never saw a benefit.
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal brutalized Hakeem Olajuwon, Charles Barkley and Antoine
Carr for 37 points. Bryant scored 24, including a devastating run
of 15 straight from the first to second quarter, celebrating
silently with a few knowing looks to his sister Shaya at courtside.
</P>
<P>
   Reid banged relentlessly at Barkley, disrupting his rhythm just
enough to hold him to 20 points. Bryant, Fox and Robert Horry took
turns slowing up Pippen, and when that wasn't enough, Reid leveled
him with a third-quarter clothesline.
</P>
<P>
   Horry came through for 12 points off the bench, and Harper gave
13.
</P>
<P>
   This is what it looks like when the Lakers get on that ``same
page'' O'Neal is always mumbling about.
</P>
<P>
   ``Before the game, we just stressed to the team that in order
for us to be successful, we had to do it as a team, at both ends of
the court,'' coach Kurt Rambis said.
</P>
<P>
   Just as they had in a six-game winning streak that preceded a
letdown and a Rockets rout in Game 3.
</P>
<P>
   They did it on a steady diet of Shaq and Kobe.
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal, frustrated the previous game, was put in motion more
often, preventing the Rockets from pushing him off the low block.
And Bryant simply got back to his aggressive style.
</P>
<P>
   ``In Game 3, I didn't play well, and I never have two bad games
in a row, and 9 for 22 (shooting) is awful,'' O'Neal said. ``After
the game, Sarge (his father) called me up and let me have it. . . .
Kobe didn't play well in Game 3, and I didn't play well in Game 3,
and neither of us like to have two bad game in a row. So both of
us, we were coming out to win.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rockets, facing elimination once again, matched the Lakers
blow for blow for most of the first quarter, but the firepower
Pippen and Barkley displayed in combining for 67 points in Game 3
never arrived this time.
</P>
<P>
   By the time Bryant's 15-point run was over, the Lakers had a
four-point lead in the second quarter. Houston would never so much
as tie the game again.
</P>
<P>
   A brutally physical Lakers defense made sure of that.
</P>
<P>
   ``This was a closing game, and closing games are not handed to
you by anybody in this league,'' Fox said, ``so we knew we had to
come in and basically take it from them.''
</P>
<P>
   That was evident in every Reid thump against Barkley.
</P>
<P>
   ``You look at J.R.'s line, he didn't score, he got nine
rebounds. People will say, `My God, the guy stinks,' '' Rambis
said. ``But realistically, I thought he did a very good job doing
what we asked him to do against a future Hall of Fame, a great
basketball player.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rockets made their best charge in the third quarter, slicing
the lead to three points, but the Lakers had an answer for
everything.
</P>
<P>
   Houston leaves the playoffs impressed.
</P>
<P>
   ``We got beat by a better team; I really believe that,'' Barkley
said. ``The Lakers have a better team than we do. Shaq is the most
dominant player the last three or four years. . . . Kobe exploded
today. Scottie, Hakeem and I would have to reach into the past to
match what we had to go against.''
</P>
</TEXT>
